'''Chenlambec''' was a [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]] [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] with rare and recessive [[Color/Legends|silvertip]] fur who fled [[Kashyyyk/Legends|Kashyyyk]] after [[Death/Legends|killing]] an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] officer for beating a Wookiee [[Youngling/Legends|child]].

==Biography==
Chenlambec became known in the hunting circles as the 'Raging Wookiee', and it was well known that he only accepted [[Death/Legends|dead]] or alive assignments. He usually opted to return to his contractor with proof of death. However, he sometimes helped his [[Agapos the Ninth|targets]] to escape to the Rebellion, and faked proof of death so that the targets would be safe from the Empire. He claimed the bounties on their 'dead bodies' as well. He wore a bandoleer of black reptile skin, so as to ward off any [[Trandoshan/Legends|Trandoshan]] hunters looking to kill him for sport.

Chen befriended [[Tinian I'att Azur-Jamin|Tinian I'att]], and became her ''Ng'rhr'', or clan-uncle. He took Tinian on as a Hunt apprentice, and they participated in three Hunts together before they decided to hunt down [[Bossk/Legends|Bossk]], the infamous Trandoshan bounty hunter. Chen and Tinian eventually formed a loose relationship with him to capture [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] after the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]]. This was actually a ruse to double-cross Bossk and entrap him in illegal Wookiee pelt-baiting in the [[Lomabu system/Legends|Lomabu system]]. Chen had a handheld [[Slicer droid/Legends|slicer droid]] named [[Flirt]].

Chen was one of the more famous bounty hunters who rose to prominence after the fall of the [[Bounty Hunters' Guild/Legends|Bounty Hunters' Guild]]. He once owned a personal [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] called the [[Wroshyr (starship)|''Wroshyr'']].

